## UX Specification

### Navigation Model
- **Primary:** Tab bar (bottom, 4-5 tabs max, thumb-reachable)
- **Secondary:** Navigation stack (push/pop, back swipe)
- **Contextual:** Long-press menus, swipe actions on list items
- **No sidebar** (unless iPad, see iPad section below)

### Thumb Zone Design
```
┌──────────────────────┐
│   STATUS / TITLE     │  ← Stretch zone (show-only, rarely tapped)
│                      │
│                      │
│   SCROLLABLE         │  ← Content zone (lists, cards, detail)
│   CONTENT            │
│                      │
│   PRIMARY ACTIONS    │  ← Natural zone (FAB, send button, key actions)
├──────────────────────┤
│      TAB BAR         │  ← Navigation (always visible)
└──────────────────────┘
```

### Progressive Disclosure
- **Level 1 — Glance:** Card/list summary (visible in list view)
- **Level 2 — Detail:** Tap to expand, full content
- **Level 3 — Advanced:** "More" button, settings, debug info

